<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="162" pageId="19" pageNumber="161" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1986,2014]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="162" pageId="19" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,388,1987,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="161">Material examined.</emphasis>
One specimen with collection number MMO 1/22 4730/253 [
<collectionCode box="[1109,1189,1986,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="161">MWO</collectionCode>
]; Baltic amber, adult, male, complete specimen with exposed distal part of genitalia and metathoracic wings; specimen partially obscured by layered structure of the amber and milky opacity (forebody). Body length of the specimen is 
<quantity box="[1221,1309,186,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="162" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. The beetle inclusion is preserved in a small-sized, yellow, polished piece of transparent amber with dimensions of 10×6× 
<quantity box="[1373,1437,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="162" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
without supplementary fixation. Syninclusions are absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="20" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,294,320]" pageId="20" pageNumber="162">Note.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[323,421,294,320]" pageId="20" pageNumber="162">holotype</typeStatus>
length is 
<quantity box="[535,626,294,321]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="20" pageNumber="162" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
. The second known exemplar of the extinct 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alekseev et Pankowski" authorityYear="2020" box="[1134,1409,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Madelinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gedanoposita">
<emphasis box="[1134,1409,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="162">Madelinia gedanoposita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctly smaller than 
<typeStatus box="[406,508,330,356]" pageId="20" pageNumber="162">holotype</typeStatus>
. The size difference between specimens is considered as intraspecific variation of a single species, such size range is normal situation among the related extant beetles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
